cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This is the most likely category, as the paper is about universal dependency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper describes a pipeline consisting of multiple machine learning models, so this category is also likely. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This category is also likely, as the paper is about developing a system that can parse natural language text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper mentions using neural networks for some of the models, so this category is also possible. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This category is less likely, but the paper does mention using convolutional neural networks for word segmentation, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision.
